                                        ],
                                        "body": "In <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/florida/fl-residential-code-2023/chapter/24/fuel-gas#flood_hazard_area\">flood hazard areas</a> as established in <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/florida/fl-residential-code-2023/chapter/3/building-planning#table_R301.2-1\">Table R301.2(1)</a>, <span class=\"u-italic\"><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/florida/fl-residential-code-2023/chapter/2/definitions#combustion_air\">combustion air</a></span> openings shall be located at or above the elevation required in <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/florida/fl-residential-code-2023/chapter/3/building-planning#R322.2.1\">Section R322.2.1</a> or <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/florida/fl-residential-code-2023/chapter/3/building-planning#R322.3.2\">R322.3.2</a>.",
